# ReelPhone design system (reelphone-com-site repo)

This rule encodes the canonical brand tokens for **reelphone.com**. ReelPhone is its own product brand under Bear LLC - distinct visual identity from the SlatePress vertical-lander family. The palette leans navy + blue (vs. SlatePress's pure-white + ink + blue).

The source of truth for these tokens is the `:root` block at the top of `index.html`. If they ever drift, this rule should be updated to match - the live file wins.

## Canonical tokens

```css
:root{
  /* Backgrounds */
  --bg:#F4F6FB;             /* primary canvas - cool paper-tinted blue */
  --bg-soft:#EDF1F8;        /* secondary surface, slightly bluer */
  --canvas:#FFFFFF;         /* card / contrast surface (high-emphasis sections) */

  /* Text */
  --ink:#0A1023;            /* primary text - near-black with navy undertone */
  --ink-soft:#384055;       /* secondary text */
  --slate:#5B6479;          /* tertiary text */
  --slate-dim:#8B93A6;      /* quaternary muted text */

  /* Borders / rules - alpha-based on ink for harmonized strokes */
  --rule:rgba(10,16,35,.07);
  --rule-strong:rgba(10,16,35,.14);

  /* Brand blue family */
  --blue:#2563EB;           /* PRIMARY brand blue */
  --blue-bright:#3B82F6;    /* lighter accent variant */
  --blue-deep:#1D4ED8;      /* hover state */
  --blue-soft:#E8EFFE;      /* tinted backgrounds, badges */
  --blue-tint:rgba(37,99,235,.08);

  /* Navy - hero / dark-mode sections */
  --navy:#0E1830;           /* dark hero background */
  --navy-deep:#080F23;      /* deepest navy */
  --navy-soft:#1A2747;      /* navy with a touch of lift */
}
```

## Type stack

**Inter only.** Single sans-serif throughout. No display serif, no monospace by default.

```css
font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, system-ui, sans-serif;
```

## Cardinal rules for reelphone-com-site

- **Cool paper canvas (`--bg #F4F6FB`).** Distinguishes ReelPhone from SlatePress's pure white. The slight blue tint signals tech-forward / device product, not local-business service.
- **Two-mode pattern.** Light sections use `--bg` / `--bg-soft` / `--canvas`. Dark hero/feature sections use `--navy` / `--navy-deep` / `--navy-soft`. Don't mix - a section is either light-mode or dark-mode end-to-end.
- **Brand blue (`--blue` #2563EB) is the one accent.** Same blue as the SlatePress family (Bear LLC house color). On light-mode sections it appears as text/CTA accent. On dark-mode sections it pops against `--navy`.
- **No new hex codes.** Especially: no greens, no oranges, no purples. The accent palette is blue-only.
- **Alpha-based rules.** Border tokens (`--rule`, `--rule-strong`) are `rgba(10,16,35,...)` so they harmonize on any background tint without specific overrides per section.
- **No gradient buttons, no carousels, no Lorem ipsum, no emoji in production UI.**
- **Hardware product, not service.** Copy and visuals should communicate device/iPhone-rig physicality. UGC video production is the use case - phone visualizations, capture-rig diagrams, brand-content output samples are appropriate. SlatePress's "trade-vertical" aesthetic (founder badges, Foundation pricing) is wrong for this site.

## Pricing

ReelPhone has its own product pricing ($1,997 setup + $1,750-2,000/mo) - distinct from the SlatePress Foundation pricing. No cross-repo pricing-sync rule applies. The offer spec lives at `offer.md` in this repo.

## When designing or reviewing UI in this repo

Defer to the `premium-web-designer` Claude skill. When it fires:
1. Ask "What are we designing today?"
2. On the answer "reelphone.com" or any edit in this repo, load the tokens above.
3. Apply universal taste principles on top.
4. Produce code that references the brand's variable names (`--blue`, `--ink`, `--bg`, `--canvas`, `--navy`) directly - never invent token names.
